<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06168005 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06168005 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  A 27-year-old transient hit by a commuter train was listed in satisfactorycondition Saturday at Kaiser-Redwood City hospital, said a nursing supervisor.The man was lying just outside the tracks when a CalTrain bound for San Joseclipped him, said Southern Pacific spokesman Mike Brown. Southern Pacificsupplies CalTrain crews. The accident happened at 9 p.m. Friday, about 500yards north of Northumberland Avenue, in an unincorporated area of RedwoodCity. A Menlo Park Fire Protection District spokeswoman said the man's leftleg was almost severed, and his right leg was twisted. The Kaiser nursingsupervisor said the man won't lose either limb. The San Mateo County Sheriff'sDepartment has not released his name.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  TRANSIENT HIT BY CALTRAIN ON PENINSULA  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Bay Area in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910616  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  7B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  121  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday June 16, 199100168005,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>